y.definition: the 25th letter of the Roman alphabet

y-axis.definition: the vertical axis in a plane coordinate system

y-shaped.definition: shaped in the form of the letter Y

yacca.definition: West Indian evergreen with medium to long leaves

yachtsman.definition: a person who owns or sails a yacht

yahoo.definition: one of a race of brutes resembling men but subject to the Houyhnhnms in a novel by Jonathan Swift

yahweh.definition: a name for the God of the Old Testament as transliterated from the Hebrew consonants YHVH

yajur-veda.definition: a collection of sacrificial formulas and prayers

yakima.definition: a town in south central Washington

yakut.definition: a member of a Turkic people of northeastern Siberia (mainly in the Lena river basin)

yale.definition: English philanthropist who made contributions to a college in Connecticut that was renamed in his honor (1649-1721)

yalta.definition: a resort city in Crimea in the southern Ukraine on the Black Sea; site of the Allied conference between Roosevelt, Stalin, and Churchill in February 1945

yalu.definition: river in eastern Asia; rises in North Korea and flows southwest to Korea Bay (forming part of the border between North Korea and China)

yam.definition: edible tuber of any of several yams

yama.definition: Hindu god of death and lord of the underworld

yamani.definition: Saudi Arabian minister of petroleum who was a central figure in the creation of OPEC (born in 1930)

yana.definition: a member of an extinct North American Indian people who lived in northern California

yanan.definition: a language group of the Hokan family

yang.definition: the bright positive masculine principle in Chinese dualistic cosmology

yank.definition: pull, or move with a sudden movement

yankee.definition: used by Southerners for an inhabitant of a northern state in the United States (especially a Union soldier)

yanker.definition: someone who gives a strong sudden pull

yard.definition: a unit of length equal to 3 feet; defined as 91.44 centimeters; originally taken to be the average length of a stride

yardage.definition: distance measured in the aggregate number of yards

yardarm.definition: either end of the yard of a square-rigged ship

yarder.definition: (used only in combinations) the height or length of something in yards

yardgrass.definition: coarse annual grass having fingerlike spikes of flowers; native to Old World tropics; a naturalized weed elsewhere

yardmaster.definition: a railroad employer who is in charge of a railway yard

yardstick.definition: a measure or standard used for comparison

yarmulke.definition: a skullcap worn by religious Jews (especially at prayer)

yarn-spinning.definition: inclined to tell long and involved stories (often of incredible happenings)

yarrow.definition: ubiquitous strong-scented mat-forming Eurasian herb of wasteland, hedgerow or pasture having narrow serrate leaves and small usually white florets; widely naturalized in North America

yashmak.definition: the face veil worn by Muslim women

yataghan.definition: a long Turkish knife with a curved blade having a single edge

yautia.definition: tropical American aroid having edible tubers that are cooked and eaten like yams or potatoes

yavapai.definition: a member of a North American Indian people of central Arizona

yaw.definition: an erratic deflection from an intended course

yawl.definition: a ship's small boat (usually rowed by 4 or 6 oars)

yawn.definition: utter a yawn, as from lack of oxygen or when one is tired

yawning.definition: gaping open as if threatening to engulf someone or something

yaws.definition: an infectious tropical disease resembling syphilis in its early stages; marked by red skin eruptions and ulcerating lesions

yay.definition: a branch of the Tai languages

yazoo.definition: a river that rises in west central Mississippi and flows southwest to empty into the Mississippi River above Vicksburg

year.definition: a period of time containing 365 (or 366) days

year-end.definition: taking place at the close of a fiscal year

year-round.definition: operating or continuing throughout the year

yearbook.definition: a book published annually by the graduating class of a high school or college usually containing photographs of faculty and graduating students

yearling.definition: a racehorse considered one year old until the second Jan. 1 following its birth

yearn.definition: have affection for; feel tenderness for

yeast.definition: a commercial leavening agent containing yeast cells; used to raise the dough in making bread and for fermenting beer or whiskey

yeasty.definition: of or resembling or containing yeast

yeatsian.definition: in the manner of William Butler Yeats

yell.definition: utter or declare in a very loud voice

yelling.definition: uttering a loud inarticulate cry as of pain or excitement

yellow.definition: of the color intermediate between green and orange in the color spectrum; of something resembling the color of an egg yolk

yellow-green.definition: of a color midway between yellow and green

yellow-tinged.definition: of a color tinged with yellow

yellow-tipped.definition: of a flower tipped with yellow

yellow-white.definition: of a white tinged with yellow

yellowcake.definition: an impure mixture of uranium oxides obtained during the processing of uranium ore

yellowfin.definition: may reach 400 pounds; worldwide in tropics

yellowhammer.definition: European bunting the male being bright yellow

yellowknife.definition: a town in the Northwest Territories in northern Canada on the Great Slave Lake

yellowlegs.definition: either of two North American shorebird with yellow legs

yellowstone.definition: a tributary of the Missouri River that flows through the Yellowstone National Park

yellowtail.definition: superior food fish of the tropical Atlantic and Caribbean with broad yellow stripe along the sides and on the tail

yellowthroat.definition: small olive-colored American warblers with yellow breast and throat

yellowwood.definition: the yellow wood of any of various yellowwood trees

yemen.definition: a republic on the southwestern shores of the Arabian Peninsula on the Indian Ocean; formed in 1990

yemeni.definition: of or relating to or characteristic of Yemen or its inhabitants

yen.definition: the basic unit of money in Japan; equal to 100 sen

yenisei.definition: a Russian river in Siberia; rises in mountains near the Mongolian border and flows generally northward into the Kara Sea

yeniseian.definition: a member of one of the groups living in the Yenisei river valley in western Siberia

yenta.definition: (Yiddish) a vulgar shrew; a shallow coarse termagant

yeoman.definition: officer in the (ceremonial) bodyguard of the British monarch

yeomanry.definition: class of small freeholders who cultivated their own land

yerkes.definition: United States psychologist who studied the intelligence of primates (1876-1956)

yeshiva.definition: an academy for the advanced study of Jewish texts (primarily the Talmud)

yevtushenko.definition: Russian poet who expressed the feelings of the post-Stalinist generation (born in 1933)

yew.definition: wood of a yew; especially the durable fine-grained light brown or red wood of the English yew valued for cabinetwork and archery bows

yggdrasil.definition: (Norse mythology) a huge ash tree whose roots and branches hold the earth and Heaven and Hell together

yiddish.definition: a dialect of High German including some Hebrew and other words; spoken in Europe as a vernacular by many Jews; written in the Hebrew script

yield.definition: be the cause or source of

yielding.definition: inclined to yield to argument or influence or control

yin.definition: the dark negative feminine principle in Chinese dualistic cosmology

yip.definition: a sharp high-pitched cry (especially by a dog)

yips.definition: nervous tension that causes an athlete to fail (especially causes golfers to miss short putts)

ylem.definition: (cosmology) the original matter that (according to the big bang theory) existed before the formation of the chemical elements

ymir.definition: (Norse mythology) the primeval giant slain by Odin and his brothers and from whose body they created the world: the sea from his blood; the earth from his flesh; the mountains from his bones; the sky from his skull

yo-yo.definition: a toy consisting of a spool that is reeled up and down on a string by motions of the hand

yodel.definition: sing by changing register; sing by yodeling

yodeling.definition: singing by changing back and forth between the chest voice and a falsetto

yodeller.definition: a singer who changes register rapidly (popular is Swiss folk songs)

yodh.definition: the 10th letter of the Hebrew alphabet

yoga.definition: Hindu discipline aimed at training the consciousness for a state of perfect spiritual insight and tranquility that is achieved through the three paths of actions and knowledge and devotion

yogi.definition: one who practices yoga and has achieved a high level of spiritual insight

yogurt.definition: a custard-like food made from curdled milk

yokel.definition: a person who is not very intelligent or interested in culture

yokohama.definition: port city on southeastern Honshu in central Japan

yokuts.definition: a member of the North American Indian people of the San Joaquin Valley

yolk.definition: nutritive material of an ovum stored for the nutrition of an embryo (especially the yellow mass of a bird or reptile egg)

yonder.definition: at or in an indicated (usually distant) place (`yon' is archaic and dialectal)

york.definition: the English royal house (a branch of the Plantagenet line) that reigned from 1461 to 1485; its emblem was a white rose

yorkshire.definition: a former large county in northern England; in 1974 it was divided into three smaller counties

yorktown.definition: a historic village in southeastern Virginia to the north of Newport News; site of the last battle of the American Revolution

yoruba.definition: a member of a West African people living chiefly in southwestern Nigeria

yosemite.definition: a series of waterfalls in Yosemite National Park in California; is reduced to a trickle for part of each year

young.definition: (used of living things especially persons) in an early period of life or development or growth

younger.definition: used of the younger of two persons of the same name especially used to distinguish a son from his father

youth.definition: the time of life between childhood and maturity

youthful.definition: suggestive of youth; vigorous and fresh

ypres.definition: battle in World War I (1917); an Allied offensive which eventually failed because tanks bogged down in the waterlogged soil of Flanders; Germans introduced mustard gas which interfered with the Allied artillery

ytterbium.definition: a soft silvery metallic element; a rare earth of the lanthanide series; it occurs in gadolinite and monazite and xenotime

yttrium.definition: a silvery metallic element that is common in rare-earth minerals; used in magnesium and aluminum alloys

yuan.definition: the basic unit of money in China

yucatan.definition: a state of Mexico on the northern part of the Yucatan Peninsula

yucatec.definition: a member of the Mayan people of the Yucatan peninsula in Mexico

yucca.definition: any of several evergreen plants of the genus Yucca having usually tall stout stems and a terminal cluster of white flowers; warmer regions of North America

yugoslav.definition: a native or inhabitant of Yugoslavia

yugoslavia.definition: a former country of southeastern Europe bordering the Adriatic Sea; formed in 1918 and named Yugoslavia in 1929; controlled by Marshal Tito as a communist state until his death in 1980

yugoslavian.definition: of or relating to or characteristic of the former country of Yugoslavia or its people or languages

yukawa.definition: Japanese mathematical physicist who proposed that nuclear forces are mediated by massive particles called mesons which are analogous to the photon in mediating electromagnetic forces (1907-1981)

yukon.definition: a North American river that flows westward from the Yukon Territory through central Alaska to the Bering Sea

yuma.definition: a member of the North American Indian people of Arizona and adjacent Mexico and California

yuman.definition: of or relating to the language or culture of the Yuma people

yuppie.definition: a young upwardly mobile professional individual; a well-paid middle-class professional who works in a city and has a luxurious life style

yurt.definition: a circular domed dwelling that is portable and self-supporting; originally used by nomadic Mongol and Turkic people of central Asia but now used as inexpensive alternative or temporary housing
